claim.claim-text:
1. A method of manufacturing a phosphate-bonded refractory product entirely during the mixing cycle by reacting phosphoric acid and alumina derived from one or more sources of finely divided reactive alumina to form a proto aluminum orthophosphate gel or paste binder in the pan of a high-intensity mixer at ambient temperatures comprising the steps of: 
a) proportioning a size-graded refractory composition including an alumina derived from one or more sources of finely divided reactive alumina; 
b) blending the ingredients to distribute the finely divided reactive alumina source uniformly through the batch; 
c) adding up to one half of the required water; 
d) adding 75 or 85 percent phosphoric acid to the mix in an amount to provide an atomic ratio of aluminum, derived from one or more sources of finely divided reactive alumina, to the phosphorus, derived from the phosphoric acid, of about 1:1; and 
e) adding the balance of the required water to obtain the desired workability.

2. A method of manufacturing a phosphate-bonded refractory product entirely during the mixing cycle by reacting phosphoric acid and one or more sources of reactive alumina derived from finely divided &bgr;-alumina and/or aluminum hydroxide to form a proto aluminum orthophosphate gel or paste binder in the pan of a high-intensity mixer at ambient temperatures comprising the steps of: 
a) proportioning a size-graded refractory composition including a source of reactive alumina derived from finely divided &bgr;-alumina and/or aluminum hydroxide; 
b) blending the ingredients to distribute the finely divided &bgr;-alumina and/or aluminum hydroxide uniformly through the batch; 
c) adding up to one half of the required water; 
d) adding 75 or 85 percent phosphoric acid to the mix in an amount to provide an atomic ratio of aluminum, derived from the &bgr;-alumina and/or aluminum hydroxide, to the phosphorus, derived from the phosphoric acid, of about 1:1; and 
e) adding the balance of the required water to obtain the desired workability.
